<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Earl of Elgin</gloss> to
                                Governor Sir <persName type="to">W.
                            MacGregor</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Downing
                                        Street</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-13"><hi rend="italic">September 13,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Referring to your telegram of the 8th September, proposals for modus
                            vivendi, including suspension of act No. 1 of this year, made to United
                            States ambassador the 3d September. Copies of correspondence went by
                            last mail.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>